block content
  h2.under 1) Write with your eraser
  p You get 100 bucks for every word you rub out from your title:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt1.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 2) Don't exaggerate
  p An honest line always feels warmer:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt2.jpg" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 3) No one cares what you can do
  p Everyone cares what you can do!{' '}
    span.italic for them
    | .
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt3.jpg" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 4) Avoid the passive voice
  p It's indirect and awkward:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt4.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 5) Don't kill your personality
  p The best brands feel “real”:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt11a.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 6) Avoid “landing page words”
  p
    span.italic Unlock
    | ,!{' '}
    span.italic unleash
    | ,!{' '}
    span.italic enhance
    | ,!{' '}
    span.italic exceed
    | ,!{' '}
    span.italic empower
    | ,!{' '}
    span.italic supercharge
    | , etc.
  p Real people don't use them.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt13.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 7) Find the tension
  p “Pleasant” gets forgotten. Conflict creates interest:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt12d.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
