  h2.under 8) Write how you talk
  p Casual. Colloquial. Full of pronouns:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt5.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 9) Avoid “contained” titles
  p Write something that pulls your reader down your page:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt14.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  //- img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt12f.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 10) Write scannable copy
  p Formatting matters:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt6.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 11) Stories make you memorable
  p I couldn't list The Ten Commandments. I could tell you what happened to Adam and Eve:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt8.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
  h2.under 12) More periods, fewer commas.
  p Periods mean short sentences. We like short sentences.
  p Commas mean long, painful sentences, like this one, which!{' '}
    span.italic New Yorker
    |!{' '}writers think are clever, but real people find torturous, because they wind on and on without actually saying anything.
  p h/t!{' '}
    a(href="https://twitter.com/david_perell/status/1250149037837176834" target="_blank") David Perell
  h2.under 13) Kill adverbs. Kill adjectives.
  p They're flowery. They're vague. They try too hard:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/ctt9.png" alt="Value-based messaging").img__100
